    <question>
        <prompt>What was the "Colfax Massacre" of 1873?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">The killing of African Americans defending a Louisiana courthouse</option>
            <option letter="b">A battle between Union and Confederate forces</option>
            <option letter="c">A labor strike that turned violent</option>
            <option letter="d">A naval engagement</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Colfax Massacre occurred when white supremacists attacked African Americans defending a courthouse in Louisiana, killing over 100 people in one of Reconstruction's bloodiest incidents.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the significance of the "Grandfather Clause" in Southern voting restrictions?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Exempted whites from voting restrictions by referring to pre-1867 voters</option>
            <option letter="b">Required all voters to prove their grandfathers voted</option>
            <option letter="c">Gave special rights to elderly voters</option>
            <option letter="d">Protected African American voting rights</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Grandfather Clause exempted whites from voting restrictions by allowing anyone whose grandfather could vote before 1867 to vote, effectively excluding African Americans.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the primary goal of the First Reconstruction Act's military districts?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To oversee the creation of new state governments and protect freedmen</option>
            <option letter="b">To punish former Confederates</option>
            <option letter="c">To manage agricultural production</option>
            <option letter="d">To collect taxes</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The military districts were established to oversee the creation of new state governments based on universal male suffrage and to protect the rights of freedmen.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>How did the Compromise of 1877 affect African Americans in the South?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Left them vulnerable to increased discrimination and violence</option>
            <option letter="b">Strengthened their voting rights</option>
            <option letter="c">Provided them with new economic opportunities</option>
            <option letter="d">Guaranteed federal protection</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Compromise of 1877's removal of federal troops left African Americans vulnerable to increased discrimination, violence, and the loss of political rights in the South.</explanation>
    </question>
